<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<circuit>
  <version>2</version>
  <attributes>
    <entry>
      <string>shapeType</string>
      <shapeType>LAYOUT</shapeType>
    </entry>
    <entry>
      <string>Description</string>
      <string>Pin multiplexer

Each physical pin can be connected to 1 or two inputs or outputs. 

O0: Choice of output for Sel=0
O1: Choice of output for Sel=1

I0: Choice of input for Sel = 0
I1: Choice of input for Sel = 1

Sel: select the input/output
DIR: Set direction: 0=output , 1=input.
NOTE: this signal selects whether the physical pin is in/out, and is seperate from the configuration of a GPIO pin direction

PIN: ... It&apos;s the pin.</string>
    </entry>
    <entry>
      <string>romContent</string>
      <romList>
        <roms/>
      </romList>
    </entry>
    <entry>
      <string>Height</string>
      <int>6</int>
    </entry>
    <entry>
      <string>Width</string>
      <int>7</int>
    </entry>
  </attributes>
